I​ really liked this course.  It's not a hardcore programming class.  It doesn't get too technical, and there are more thorough introductions to C programming on here.  The beautiful thing about this class is that it gets you started thinking about programming by applying the basic idea of algorithms to everyday tasks and then you write simple programs in C.  It gets you started without overwhelming you.
